│  US Supreme Court justices (SCOTUS) ruled 6 to 3 in favor of striking down President Trump's sweeping       │
│  trade tariffs on Friday, finding these policies were not authorized under IEEPA (International Emergency   │
│  Economic Powers Act). Trump called the decision "deeply disappointing" at a press conference earlier       │
│  today while planning to push for new 10% global tariffs as an alternative. Nazak Nikakhtar, chair and      │
│  partner for Wiley Rein's National Security Practice, comes on Market Domination to help define the         │
│  executive branch's tariff authorities outlined in IEEPA and comment on whether SCOTUS could force the      │
│  administration to refund tariffs. Nikakhtar also served as the US Department of Commerce's Assistant       │
│  Secretary and Under Secretary in the first Trump administration. To watch more expert insights and         │
│  analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination. For more predictions market        │
│  insight, check out the new Yahoo Finance Polymarket Hub. For more on the Supreme Court's tariff ruling,    │
